			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I realize this is a rant, but this is a direct result of our political debate.<br />
<br />
But seriously, fuck this country and fuck the republicans.<br />
<br />
I'm self employed, my wife is self employed.  Because of this we have health insurance through the health exchange (in Ohio).  I'm already mad enough that our monthly premium is $440 for a family of 4, which is outrageous.  Anytime I hear someone speak out against universal health coverage I just want to punch them in their face.  And I don't understand why people are so willing to pay so much money for such crappy coverage.<br />
<br />
Despite all this I was in a good mood because my step daughter recently got married and we were taking her off our plan.  So I think great, I can save a little money.<br />
<br />
Boy was I wrong.  Our plan went UP $130 to remove the most expensive person on the plan (she has severe asthma and mental issues).  So now they want me to pay $570 or something a month to insure 3 whole people.<br />
<br />
On top of that I have very little power to fight any of it.  Hell, I can't even talk to anyone that can make a decision.  The health insurance company won't talk to me directly about policy changes.  They direct you to the health exchange.  The health exchange has no say or control over pricing though, they just tell you what the companies are quoting them.<br />
<br />
It's a circle jerk designed to strip me of any power.  They said my only recourse is to search for a different plan or file an appeal that takes 90 days.<br />
<br />
And all of this for coverage that is crappy at best, my wife was even denied a biopsy the doctor wanted to do last month.  <b>A procedure requested by a medical specialist was denied by the insurance company</b>.  If we were told 10 years ago that our premiums would skyrocket up, our copays would skyrocket up and fewer things would be covered people would have lost their minds.  But somehow we're still here and most of this country seems fine with it.<br />
<br />
Health insurance for profit is the worst idea this country has ever had.  And the republicans have ensured that the free market is so hands off we see a negative economic benefit to it.  My own dad hates the idea of everyone in this country having health insurance, even though he knows his own son would be without it if republicans had their way.<br />
<br />
So basically I just had a conversation that ended with me threatening to murder the manager.  And honestly I'm even more pissed that Bernie isn't getting elected now.  I'm also mad that Obama pussied out when he had the chance.</div>

