I turn 47 in April by the way.  The cardiologist cleared me to return to work the first week of April, with zero restrictions.  -Said I could start lifting again in 2 months, lower weight and higher reps.  I haven't had a cigarette since it happened, and I'm on a low sodium / low cholesterol diet now which I think I'm struggling with more than the smoking, heh.<br />
<br />
This kind of served as a wake up call I think to alot of friends, colleagues and family who've been asking lots of questions.  I'm certainly willing to answer any here if any have any.<br />
<br />
And if any here have gone through stuff like this I'd be curious to hear about it.  I wouldn't turn down any mojo sent my way either.<br />
